OL,7,FWhen I was approached by Channel 4's
OL,8,FDispatches team to take part in a
OL,9,Fdocumentary about the ongoing NHS
OL,10,Fcrisis, I already knew that I couldn't
OL,11,Fcontinue in my job much longer. As an
OL,12,Femergency medical technician with the
OL,13,FEast of England Ambulance Service,
OL,14,Fattending 999 calls together with a
OL,15,Fparamedic, I was frustrated at the way
OL,16,Four patients were suffering from delays
OL,17,Fand short-staffing. It was having a
OL,18,Fdetrimental effect on my wellbeing too.
OL,3,CI recorded patients suffering from NHS
OL,4,Cdelays - the public needs to see how
OL,5,Cbad it is
